  "text": "JavaScript Parsing to Bytecode Chain in Mozilla SpiderMonkey:\n\nThe SpiderMonkey JavaScript engine compiles JavaScript source text into bytecode through a multi-stage pipeline:\n\n1. ENTRY POINT: CompileGlobalScript (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.h:126-148)\n   - Main public API for compiling global JavaScript source text\n   - Accepts ReadOnlyCompileOptions and SourceText\n   - Returns JSScript containing compiled bytecode\n\n2. COMPILATION ORCHESTRATION: ScriptCompiler class (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:172-200)\n   - Template class that manages the compilation pipeline\n   - Creates and coordinates parser and bytecode emitter\n   - ScriptCompiler::compile() method (line 955) orchestrates: parsing → AST → bytecode emission\n\n3. LEXICAL ANALYSIS: TokenStream (js/src/frontend/TokenStream.h/cpp)\n   - Converts source text into tokens\n   - Handles character-by-character analysis\n   - Produces token stream for parser\n\n4. PARSING: Parser (js/src/frontend/Parser.h/cpp)\n   - Parser<FullParseHandler, Unit>::globalBody() (js/src/frontend/Parser.cpp:1867) is the key entry point\n   - Performs syntactic analysis\n   - Builds Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)\n   - Creates ParseContext and SharedContext for tracking scope and bindings\n\n5. AST NODES: ParseNode (js/src/frontend/ParseNode.h)\n   - Base class: ParseNode (line 200+)\n   - Subclasses define specific statement/expression types:\n     * UnaryNode: expressions like negation, typeof\n     * BinaryNode: operations like addition, logical ops\n     * ListNode: comma expressions, arrays, objects\n     * FunctionNode: function declarations/expressions\n     * TernaryNode: conditional expressions\n     * And 100+ other node types (FOR_EACH_PARSE_NODE_KIND macro at line 63)\n   - All nodes allocated in LifoAlloc for efficient bulk deallocation\n   - Tree lifetime tied to parser lifetime\n\n6. BYTECODE EMISSION: BytecodeEmitter (js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.h/cpp)\n   - BytecodeEmitter class processes AST nodes\n   - Main method: emitScript(ParseNode* body) (js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.cpp:2354)\n   - Walks the AST and generates JSOp bytecode instructions\n   - Manages bytecode sections (prologue and main)\n   - Handles scope and binding emission\n   - Emits jump instructions for control flow\n   - Uses helper emitter classes for specific constructs:\n     * BytecodeControlStructures for loops/conditionals\n     * CallOrNewEmitter for function calls\n     * ObjectEmitter for object literals\n     * FunctionEmitter for function definitions\n\n7. BYTECODE INSTRUCTIONS: JSOp (js/src/vm/Opcodes.h)\n   - Defines all VM opcodes (e.g., JSOp::Add, JSOp::Call, JSOp::JumpTarget)\n   - Each opcode specified with:\n     * op (UpperCamelCase): e.g., Add, Call\n     * op_snake (snake_case): e.g., add, call\n     * Operand count (nuses: stack values consumed, ndefs: produced)\n     * Format flags for operand layout\n   - Instructions are packed as single-byte opcode + variable operands\n\n8. BYTECODE OUTPUT: JSScript (js/src/vm/JSScript.h/cpp)\n   - JSScript::Create() (js/src/vm/JSScript.cpp:2526) creates compiled script objects\n   - Stores:\n     * Bytecode array (code() method)\n     * Atoms table (immutable strings)\n     * GC things (objects, functions, regexps)\n     * Source notes (mapping bytecode to source positions)\n     * Scope information\n     * Try/catch/finally notes\n   - Used by the JavaScript VM interpreter and JITs for execution\n\nKEY COMPILE STAGES:\n- Stage 0: Source Text Input (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:341)\n  CompileGlobalScriptToStencilAndMaybeInstantiate creates ScriptCompiler\n\n- Stage 1: Parsing (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:977)\n  parser->globalBody() produces ParseNode* AST\n\n- Stage 2: Bytecode Emission (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:1009)\n  emitter->emitScript(pn) generates bytecode from AST\n\n- Stage 3: Instantiation (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:345-347)\n  ConvertGlobalScriptStencilMaybeInstantiate creates JSScript from bytecode\n\nEXAMPLE FLOW FOR 'var x = 5;':\n1. CompileGlobalScript receives source \"var x = 5;\"\n2. TokenStream produces tokens: VAR, IDENTIFIER(x), ASSIGN, NUMBER(5), SEMICOLON\n3. Parser.globalBody creates VarStmt node with child AssignExpr(x, 5)\n4. BytecodeEmitter traverses AST, emits JSOp::DefVar, JSOp::String(\"x\"), JSOp::Number(5), JSOp::Init\n5. JSScript created containing these opcodes executable by the VM"
}

